elements.title: First Captain
elements.contents: ... that the first Asian-American at West Point to be named First Captain of the cadets was John Tien (pictured), the current U.S. Deputy Secretary of Homeland Security?

elements.title: Irene Parlby
elements.contents: ... that Irene Parlby was one of The Famous Five, a group of women in Canada who fought for the right of women to be considered "persons"?

elements.title: agriculture ranks as one of the most stressful occupations in the United States
elements.contents: ... that agriculture ranks as one of the most stressful occupations in the United States and one that experiences high suicide rates?

elements.title: Sophia Reid-Gantzert
elements.contents: ... that The Baby-Sitters Club actress Sophia Reid-Gantzert won an Austrian ballet competition when she was six?

elements.title: the El Dorado
elements.contents: ... that when the pastor of an African-American church bought the El Dorado, one newspaper wrote that "its occupants are white, and were white"?

elements.title: Hilda Hanbury
elements.contents: ... that actress Hilda Hanbury was the grandmother of actors James and Edward Fox and the great-grandmother of actress Emilia Fox?

elements.title: Princeton–Deepwater District
elements.contents: ... that part of West Virginia's Princeton–Deepwater District railway was so steep that only shortened coal trains could ascend it?

elements.title: George Allsopp
elements.contents: ... that George Allsopp was arrested three times for not carrying a lantern?
